'''Helen Szamuely''' (1950–2017) was a [[historian]] and [[Euroscepticism|Eurosceptic]] who was a researcher for the [[Bruges Group (United Kingdom)|Bruges Group]] and founder of the [[Anti-Federalist League]].<ref name=Times/><ref name=DT/> She was the daughter of [[Tibor Szamuely (historian)|Tibor Szamuely]]. After the [[Maastricht Treaty]] was signed in 1992, she organised monthly meetings at the [[Red Lion, Westminster|Red Lion]] near Parliament to discuss Europe.<ref name=ECBP/>
