'''Kepa Hamuera Anaha Ehau''' (5 November 1885 &ndash; 10 February 1970) was a [[New Zealand]] tribal leader, law clerk, [[interpreter]], [[soldier]], [[historian]], orator. He was born on November 5, 1885.<ref name="DNZB Ehau">{{DNZB|title=Kepa Hamuera Anaha Ehau|first= Manu H.|last= Pene|id=4e5|accessdate=6 February 2012}}</ref>

