The '''Osemawe of Ondo Kingdom''' is the paramount Yoruba king of [[Ondo Kingdom]] a city in [[Ondo State]], southwestern [[Nigeria]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punchng.com/news/jonathan-eulogises-osemawe-for-promoting-peace/|title=Jonathan eulogises Osemawe for promoting peace|work=The Punch - Nigeria's Most Widely Read Newspaper|accessdate=13 January 2015}}</ref> The "Osemawe title" was coined from the phrase "Ese-omo-re" adopted from the comment made by the late ''Alaafin  Oluaso'' during the birth of his daughter called Olu pupupu who later settled in Ondo Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thenationonlineng.net/new/a-towns-rich-history/|title=A town’s rich history|author=Our Reporter|work=The Nation|accessdate=13 January 2015}}</ref> The people of [[Ondo Kingdom]] are generally called ''Ekimogun Egi''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailyindependentnig.com/2014/09/osemawe-becomes-chairman-ondo-council-obas/|title=Osemawe becomes Chairman, Ondo Council of Obas|work=Daily Independent, Nigerian Newspaper|accessdate=13 January 2015}}</ref>

==History==
The Osemawe title of [[Ondo Kingdom]] was instituted in 1510, when princess Pupupu, a powerful daughter of the late Alaafin of [[Oyo Empire|Oyo]], king Oluaso left the palace with the royal entourage in a bid to settle far from her father's palace.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://agoiwoye.org/history-of-ondo-town/|title=History of Ondo Town|author=Ajibola|work=Ago-Iwoye! The Legend|accessdate=13 January 2015}}</ref>
She settled on a hill called ''Oke Agunla'' in [[Ondo Kingdom|Ondo town]]
On arrival of this princess at ''Oke Ogunla'' a smoke rising from far below was spotted by a man called ''Esiri'' who traced the smoke to know its source.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ekimogundescendant.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=58:-the-genesis-of-ondo-kingdom&catid=34:articles&Itemid=53|title=The Genesis of Ondo Kingdom|author=Administrator|publisher=|accessdate=13 January 2015}}</ref> On getting to the hill where the smoke was spotted, he met princess Pupupu and her royal entourage. He took them to a village in [[Ondo Kingdom]] called ''Oriden''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com.ng/books?id=GebTAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA44&lpg=PA44&dq=History+of+Osemawe+Title&source=bl&ots=OXtLqWAHS7&sig=-v0YPCiuWs413MVOO-kvtjNfX4A&hl=en&sa=X&ei=AY-1VKO2Bcf3O6vUgfAD&redir_esc=y|title=Things Fall Apart?|publisher=|accessdate=13 January 2015}}</ref> The villagers were very happy to meet the powerful princess and exclaimed Edo du do, edo do, idi edo!!! Where the name of the Kingdom  [[Ondo Kingdom]] was formed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.nl/books?id=Pq5wGaae5qkC&pg=PA356&lpg=PA356&dq=History+of+Osemawe+Title&source=bl&ots=eekw67zgGx&sig=xmebMT6bRFg57iC5R5tX70HVMAw&hl=en&sa=X&ei=U421VKDrNcTYPej4gJgN&ved=0CBwQ6AEwBw|title=Writing African History|publisher=|accessdate=13 January 2015}}</ref>

